Is that OK with you?

00:36:47.153 --> 00:36:48.910
I thought, sure.

00:36:48.910 --> 00:36:51.740
I mean I knew the
internet was-- I mean you

00:36:51.740 --> 00:36:54.650
guys were born with it and
you actually make the internet

00:36:54.650 --> 00:37:01.730
now-- but I wasn't, so
for me to see people

00:37:01.730 --> 00:37:04.280
baking-- I mean I thought
only my mother, the non baker,

00:37:04.280 --> 00:37:05.020
bought my books.

00:37:05.020 --> 00:37:06.869
But you know, I
looked on the internet

00:37:06.869 --> 00:37:08.660
and there were people
baking from my books,

00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:11.080
making beautiful things
and posting pictures,

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:12.370
and I was so excited.

00:37:12.370 --> 00:37:14.080
That's actually why
I started my blog,

00:37:14.080 --> 00:37:16.982
to be able to be in touch
with all these people.

00:37:16.982 --> 00:37:18.940
And so when Lori said
she was going to do this,

00:37:18.940 --> 00:37:20.640
I thought, oh,
this is just great.

00:37:20.640 --> 00:37:24.280
And I asked my editor, and
she said, yeah, and my agent,

00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:26.690
sure, why not?

00:37:26.690 --> 00:37:29.170
None of us thought, what
are the repercussions

00:37:29.170 --> 00:37:34.080
of having every recipe in
your book available online?

00:37:34.080 --> 00:37:36.060
We just thought, oh
this was really fun,

00:37:36.060 --> 00:37:38.120
and it's only three people.

00:37:38.120 --> 00:37:41.270
Well, they called their
group Tuesdays with Dorie,

00:37:41.270 --> 00:37:44.040
and there were
only three people.

00:37:44.040 --> 00:37:46.750
And then there were 30,
and then there were 300,

00:37:46.750 --> 00:37:49.960
and then there were thousands
of people baking their way

00:37:49.960 --> 00:37:53.250
through "Baking From
My Home to Yours."

00:37:53.250 --> 00:37:57.640
Oprah wrote about the group,
"The Wall Street Journal"

00:37:57.640 --> 00:38:01.560
wrote about the group,
and it was so special

00:38:01.560 --> 00:38:03.440
because I didn't start it.

00:38:03.440 --> 00:38:05.970
This is really-- to me
this is like the power

00:38:05.970 --> 00:38:08.530
of the inter-- my
husband always says

00:38:08.530 --> 00:38:10.870
it's the internet at its best.

00:38:10.870 --> 00:38:13.720
It just grew organically.

00:38:13.720 --> 00:38:16.810
It wasn't me saying,
gee wouldn't it

00:38:16.810 --> 00:38:19.980
be great if I had a group
who-- and so they baked

00:38:19.980 --> 00:38:23.000
their way through "Baking
From My Home to Yours,"

00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:25.430
and then they started
on-- and they're still

00:38:25.430 --> 00:38:28.540
baking through--
"Baking with Julia."

00:38:28.540 --> 00:38:32.180
And then when "Around My
French Table" came out in 2010,

00:38:32.180 --> 00:38:35.429
they started a group called
French Fridays with Dorie,

00:38:35.429 --> 00:38:37.220
and they're cooking
their way through that.

